I also removed the same catch block from method `zkUtils.deletePathRecursive`.

The related zkClient method also handles the ZkNoNodeException:
```
public boolean deleteRecursive(String path) {
        List<String> children;
        try {
            children = getChildren(path, false);
        } catch (ZkNoNodeException e) {
            return true;
        }

        for (String subPath : children) {
            if (!deleteRecursive(path + "/" + subPath)) {
                return false;
            }
        }

        return delete(path);
    }
```
